Disease comment: HPS1-7 are involved in Hermansky-Pudlak syndrome (HPS), which  comprises at least seven different autosomal recessive disorders (referred to as HPS-1 through -7) that share the clinical manifestations of oculocutaneous albinism combined with platelet storage pool deficiency and do not present with the severe immunodeficiency and giant intracellular granules characteristic of Chediak-Higashi syndrome.
